<div class="c230_5"> 
<div id="v230.5.1"><span class="H5329 s">To the chief Musician</span><span class="H5155 s"> upon Nehiloth</span><span class="H4210 s">, A Psalm</span><span class="H1732 s"> of David</span><span class="H238 s">. Give ear</span><span class="H561 s"> to my words</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H995 s">, consider</span><span class="H1901 s"> my meditation</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.5.2"><span class="H7181 s">Hearken</span><span class="H6963 s"> unto the voice</span><span class="H7773 s"> of my cry</span><span class="H4428 s">, my King</span><span class="H430 s">, and my God</span><span class="H6419 s">: for unto thee will I pray</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.5.3"><span class="H6963 s">My voice</span><span class="H8085 s"> shalt thou hear</span><span class="H1242 s"> in the morning</span><span class="H3068 s">, O LORD</span><span class="H1242 s">; in the morning</span><span class="H6186 s"> will I direct</span><span class="H6822 s"> <i>my prayer</i> unto thee, and will look up</span>.</div> 
<div id="v230.5.4"><span class="H410 s">For thou <i>art</i> not a God</span><span class="H2655 s"> that hath pleasure</span><span class="H7562 s"> in wickedness</span><span class="H7451 s">: neither shall evil</span><span class="H1481 s"> dwell</span> with thee.</div> 
<div id="v230.5.5"><span class="H1984 s">The foolish</span><span class="H3320 s"> shall not stand</span><span class="H5869 s"> in thy sight</span><span class="H8130 s">: thou hatest</span><span class="H6466 s"> all workers</span><span class="H205 s"> of iniquity</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (in…: Heb. before thine eyes)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.6"><span class="H6 s">Thou shalt destroy</span><span class="H1696 s"> them that speak</span><span class="H3577 s"> leasing</span><span class="H3068 s">: the LORD</span><span class="H8581 s"> will abhor</span><span class="H1818 s"> the bloody</span><span class="H4820 s"> and deceitful</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bloody…: Heb. man of bloods and deceit)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.7"><span class="H935 s">But as for me, I will come</span><span class="H1004 s"> <i>into</i> thy house</span><span class="H7230 s"> in the multitude</span><span class="H2617 s"> of thy mercy</span><span class="H3374 s">: <i>and</i> in thy fear</span><span class="H7812 s"> will I worship</span><span class="H6944 s"> toward thy holy</span><span class="H1964 s"> temple</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (thy holy…: Heb. the temple of thy holiness)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.8"><span class="H5148 s">Lead</span><span class="H3068 s"> me, O LORD</span><span class="H6666 s">, in thy righteousness</span><span class="H8324 s"> because of mine enemies</span><span class="H1870 s">; make thy way</span><span class="H3474 s"> straight</span><span class="H6440 s"> before my face</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mine…: Heb. those which observe me)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.9"><span class="H3559 s">For <i>there is</i> no faithfulness</span><span class="H6310 s"> in their mouth</span><span class="H7130 s">; their inward</span><span class="H1942 s"> part <i>is</i> very wickedness</span><span class="H1627 s">; their throat</span><span class="H6605 s"> <i>is</i> an open</span><span class="H6913 s"> sepulchre</span><span class="H2505 s">; they flatter</span><span class="H3956 s"> with their tongue</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (faithfulness: or, stedfastness) (their mouth: Heb. his mouth, that is, the mouth of any of them) (very…: Heb. wickednesses)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.10"><span class="H816 s">Destroy</span><span class="H430 s"> thou them, O God</span><span class="H5307 s">; let them fall</span><span class="H4156 s"> by their own counsels</span><span class="H5080 s">; cast them out</span><span class="H7230 s"> in the multitude</span><span class="H6588 s"> of their transgressions</span><span class="H4784 s">; for they have rebelled</span> against thee. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Destroy…: or, Make them guilty) (by…: or, from their counsels)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.11"><span class="H2620 s">But let all those that put their trust</span><span class="H8055 s"> in thee rejoice</span><span class="H5769 s">: let them ever</span><span class="H7442 s"> shout for joy</span><span class="H5526 s">, because thou defendest</span><span class="H157 s"> them: let them also that love</span><span class="H8034 s"> thy name</span><span class="H5970 s"> be joyful</span> in thee. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (defendest…: Heb. coverest over, or, protectest them)</span></div> 
<div id="v230.5.12"><span class="H3068 s">For thou, LORD</span><span class="H1288 s">, wilt bless</span><span class="H6662 s"> the righteous</span><span class="H7522 s">; with favour</span><span class="H5849 s"> wilt thou compass</span><span class="H6793 s"> him as <i>with</i> a shield</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (compass: Heb. crown)</span></div></div> 
